## Progress
- Attempted to share WorldModel across agents — REVERTED
  - Each agent uses agent-relative coordinates (not true global)
  - Sharing causes agents to navigate to wrong positions
  - Previous sessions noted this as a bug but it's actually by design
- Deep analysis of 0-score wipeouts found ROOT CAUSE:
  - Gear station contention: all agents rush to gear stations at step 1
  - Agents that arrive but can't get gear (hub depleted) wait forever
  - FIX: step away and retry, or mine if team can't afford gear
- Implemented staggered pressure budget: 3 aligners at start, 5 after step 20
- Station retry fix: when at station without gear, step off and back on
- Stronger hub proximity bias for junction targeting (closer = better)
- Heart batch 3 default, 4 after step 3000 (was 2/3)
- 3x 10k test: 1.87, 0.57, 1.37 = avg 1.27
  - Lower than previous best (2.55 avg) but zero 0-score wipeouts
  - Variance from bad maps (ships close to hub) remains the #1 issue
- v48 uploaded to tournament
- Key learnings:
  - agent-relative coordinates mean WorldModel can't be shared
  - Gear stations are shared resources — contention is a real issue
  - Hub proximity is key — close junctions score more reliably
  - Economy needs 3+ miners to sustain 5 aligners long-term
